You don’t have to take it all on. 
We all have opinions. We all have thoughts. And as humans we connect by sharing. But you know what’s amazing, you don’t have to take it all on my friend.

Release what doesn’t work for you. 
Release the bad energy. 
Release and loosen your grip.

And this, truly is a muscle worth cultivating. Keep what works for you and release the rest. 

Thank you to my soul sister @kimknievel who gave me an Akashic Records reading sharing and reminding me of my truths. If you’re curious about learning more from her, do it! She is the kindest most truthful person in my life who delivers it with grace and the purest intentions. 

PS: to my @nicolemiyuki_kids people, thank you for your thoughts on my last holy leaves pattern. I’m feeling more aligned with this new one! 
.

Happy belated birthday Christmas boy @keenanaitchison (Yes his birthday is on Christmas!) 

You bring so much joy to this world and I don’t think you give yourself enough credit.

This year you’ve brought me a life I didn’t know was meant for me. Becoming a wife, a bonus parent, and a soon-to-be mom to a little one. And more than that, everyday life with you is a new adventure and seeing how you fearlessly love those 2 little girls is my favorite. Thank you for being our safe space 🤍👨🏻‍🍳😴🤵🏻‍♂️💍🚛🤰🏻👷🏻‍♂️

I wasn’t ready to share this until now, and warning it might bring about some emotions.

My Grandma Lucy was and is my favorite person in this whole world and this is how I told her I was pregnant 🤍

Forever thankful for this kind nurse who let me video call her the day before she passed. And for anyone else who is journeying through grief, the wisest advice I ever got was “grief is not linear.” 🤍🤍🤍

37 weeks today 🤍

I asked Keenan to take some sunrise photos of me so I could capture my growing belly.

But I now see that these photos are actually a reflection of how I’ve grown as a human being…how my heart has evolved. I feel my heart settling - in comfort, in ease, in bliss, in believing, in building on a foundation and a journey I didn’t know was ever going to happen for me.

At 33, I was one of the last of my friends to get married and have kids. So naturally, I used to think I was behind in life and something was wrong. 

But now I know, I’m right on time for me, and for this little one. And as I step into a new unknown of when this baby will arrive, how birth will go, how my body will feel, what this baby will look like - I am leaning into all of this with a person I’m so thankful for and a man I already know is an amazing father @keenanaitchison @theabunchcrew

Designing nursery art for baby’s room and felt perfect to share on a Sunday church day. 

Oh, and to all my California people, snooowwwwwwww!!

1/9 
For those of you on baby watch with us, no baby yet! I haven’t felt contractions yet (or at least I don’t think I have). So who knows when baby is coming! But I’ve been super lucky this whole pregnancy with how I’ve been feeling, so I’m allowing my body to continue doing its thing for now.

*Warning* it feels like the perfect story time so here it goes :)

2/9 
For those of you who may not know, @keenanaitchison has 2 beautiful daughters. So, when we got married in April I became their bonus mom. They are sweet and kind and spunky and rambunctious and I love them SO much.

I grew up with step-parents myself so I understand feelings as a child of divorce. I won’t go into details but I know. As I stepped into this role, I took it head on. I knew what I didn’t want to be like and I had to trust a lot in both myself and in Keenan. And gosh I am so thankful because these girls are actually the ones that have taken ME in as family 🤍 

PS: if you want to follow our family adventures we started @theabunchcrew to share!

3/9
In my career, some of you have seen me ebb and flow, pivot and wander. I started sharing my lettering in 2012 and it became my thing. It was what I did, what I was defined by in this Instagram world. In 2018 I was given an amazing opportunity to become an author and write 2 how-to books teaching lettering to both adults and kids - By Hand and @thekidsbookofhandlettering with my editor @sleefab 🤍 That was a huge defining moment in my career that I am forever grateful for!

5/9
In 2020, it was on my heart to start a kids program with @letsgomakeart so @letsmakeartkids was born 🎨 I saw that schools were cutting art programs and kids needed a space to be creative and use color! LMA kids has been my passion for the past 2 years and seeing all the kids we’ve impacted from our video tutorials - there are no words how cool it is! And recently @keenanaitchison and I got to film with kids from the community and it was SO MUCH FUN! @mandy_pittsnoggle and @nursemommapaints 😘 

PS: I’m not going anywhere with @letsmakeartkids so don’t fret, we have things filmed and ready while I’m on maternity leave so keep sharing with me when you and your kids paint with us!

6/9
Back to life, I had absolutely NO PLANS to ever move out to Missouri. I am a California girl through and through - you all know how much I love to ocean. But in 2021, the camera guy named @keenanaitchison became the person I didn’t know I was meant to be with. He became a home, my home. We got married in April 2022, moved me cross country in May, found out we were pregnant in June and are now about to bring a little one into this world in 2023. WILD and I love it and him SO MUCH.

7/9
I’m learning that God has been with me every step of the way. Leading and guiding me to and through a life that is more than my own. And as I sit here, on the baby’s due date, I know things are about to change. My life is forever going to be different and I know I will continue to be shown that things won’t happen on my own schedule. But you know what, I am okay with that now.

I’ve learned to trust my instincts, to lean on others, and that life will unfold as it’s supposed to. And the timing of this baby’s arrival is just the beginning of it 🤍

8/9
And as I step into this new stage and title of being called mama, I also feel a new season of my art career being birthed. It’s been so much fun using my illustration and graphic design background to create the patterns I’ve been sharing on @nicolemiyuki_kids ✨ 

And then designing and printing my wallpaper with a print on demand site called @spoonflower has forsure sparked something in me! I have a feeling this is just the beginning and we’ll see what happens :)

9/9
And last but not least, I want to say thank you to this community here. I’ve connected with so many of you beyond just this little app. I believe that there’s still good to be shared here, and I hope that together we can remind each other that kindness wins and that being real and vulnerable doesn’t have to be scary. 

I promise I will still be the same girl that gets deep at times, and I will still share lettering as it flows through my life. But I also know I’ll be sharing about this little babe that is about to join this world. So get ready!

No baby yet! But here’s a gem of a photo to ease the waiting 🤰🏻

Do you want to see videos of what is going on here?? 😂😂😂

Contractions have started so my body is doing something! But I wanted to make sure before I go into labor that I say a heartfelt thank you to you here.

I truly believe we are the sum of the people around us and gosh, this baby is surrounded by so much love already. If you’ve sent a message, said prayers, left a comment, or are one of my friends who have helped answer any and all of my baby questions - THANK YOU.

PS: for my people, my thank you cards will be going out after baby and maybe I’ll print out a little photo of babe so it’s an announcement card too! 

Much love 🤍

Dear baby,
As you make your way into this world, know that I’ll be on this new adventure with you. I know it’s going to be new and scary, but I promise to be right by your side. 

Thank you for choosing me to be your mama. For choosing this moment to arrive, and I promise we can do this.

You are joining a family with 2 sweet girls who are going to love you like no other and a daddy who literally is so eager to meet you and love on you. PS: If you’re a boy, game over. You’re in for the ride of your life :) 

We’re ready for you little one 🤍

Introducing our sweet boy:

Koda Ray 
Born on 2/3/23 at 1:18am
8lbs 6oz
20.5in 
with a full head of brown hair!

We took a few days to pick his name to see what felt fitting for him. Keenan kept saying he looked like my grandpa Ray which I loved as his middle name 🤍
And then Koda was 1 of 3 boy names we had. Koda means friend in Japanese and yes also from the movie Brother Bear 🐻 and it just felt so right for this little cuddly boy! 

Thank you for all of your prayers and thoughts and gosh what a wild experience birth is! It happened quick and all I can say is I’m thankful for a birthing ball and our nurses who coached me through it. The exhaustion is real but so is all the love and baby snuggles!!

A glimpse into our life for the past week with Koda Ray! So much to share, but only 10 photos so I’ll post more in my stories :)

Also because you know I share the real, day 3 and 4 were rough. Koda was loosing more weight, he hadn’t pooped for 48 hours, I was exhausted and felt out of control and helpless. 

What helped? A supportive husband and reaching out to my mama friends. Learning more about their breast feeding experiences helped me not feel alone and that I wasn’t doing something wrong. So thank you to my people and know that if you’re going through something or had a hard experience, you aren’t alone. This motherhood thing is magical and mysterious wrapped in a cute little bundle of joy. 
.
.
.
.
#dailydoseofkodaray #newborn #postpartum #motherhood #motherhoodjourney #newbornphotography #newbornbaby #milestonecards

Overthinking, running circles in your head, so many thoughts but no action. Is that you too?

As new things have happened in my career and I need to pivot, I’ve been overwhelmed and sad. This morning, I listened to a podcast with @bonniechristine and @amyporterfield that reminded me that clarity comes from action. So, here’s me taking action and showing up. 

I’m not sure the exact next step in my career, but I’m going to start with what I know best - lettering my feelings and hope that clarity will come from it.

#greatgrandpa #dailydoseofkodaray #dailyreminder #handlettering

I am learning that the world of breast feeding is vast and so personal. I’ve had friends where breast feeding was natural and then some where it was painful. I know others who can’t produce and some who overproduce. Some who do formula and others who do a combo. And then some who only pump like me. 

May I continue to be thankful for what the human body does. 

It was a journey to get to this point to find a groove of what works for Koda and I. Those early days syringe feeding to get him to gain back his weight were a lot. Me trying and waiting for him to hopefully latch better. Me being confused at how different each side produces. And then Koda and I realizing that he is healthy with our routine so let’s just keep going because it works for us! 

To all the mamas past and present we are doing it! No matter the form of feeding - breast or bottle, milk or formula, may we continue to be thankful for the wonderful world of mama hood.

PS: thank you to all my friends who have helped me along this journey. I love you all and shoutout to @vogenator for letting me borrow your pump. And the biggest love to @keenanaitchison for jumping all in 😘

#motherhood #postpartum #breastfeedingjourney #baby #dailydoseofkodaray

This past week you all saw Koda meet my family in California and it was just want my heart needed 🤍

But I did miss my Grandma immensely. She was my favorite human. Her smile radiated and her sassy comments made us giggle because it came out of nowhere! She always reminded me to not work too hard and to be happy.

I’m getting teary eyed as I write this because as I left my Grandpas I told Keenan how thankful I was that he got to meet his great grandson. My Grandpa LOVED spending time with Koda and was so good with him. During our stay he said several times “Grandma would have loved Koda” and each time it was simultaneously a warm hug and a somber reality. 

But I know one thing I can do - continue to honor my Grandma and tell Koda about her as he grows up. Because I can’t help but think a piece of her lives in Koda and why he is such a joyful smiley baby 🤍🤍

#iloveyougrandma #grandparentsarethebest #greatgrandson #japaneseamerican #japanese

There’s been a lot of changes recently and most of them ones I cannot control. You might have noticed me weave in and out of a different kind of grief and it had to do with the Kids Program ending that I did with @letsmakeartkids and @letsgomakeart.

I started the program in 2020 because my heart believed in creating a space for kids to create art. I am thankful that Let’s Make Art allowed me to pivot from teaching lettering to teaching kids and together we created over 45 boxes and 200+ tutorials! 

To both the LMA lettering and kids community, thank you ❤️. I have so enjoyed seeing you and your kids beaming faces of delight with finished art projects! You all have impacted me in more ways than I can express and I have grown tremendously alongside this group. 

I will miss the community dearly, but hopefully we can connect in a different way more personally in the future :) Keenan and I have grown so fond of the community and we are sad things had to come to an end. But as a lot of you have reminded me, when one door closes another door opens. Something is brewing in my heart and I promise to share soon.

PS: if it weren’t for @sarahdandelioncray (❤️ you) DMing me in 2018 to visit Missouri to teach lettering, I would not have had this life with Keenan, his girls and little Koda. 

May I continue to accept the changes I cannot control and be open to what comes next for us. So much love 🎨👩🏻‍🎨🌟

#kidsart #kidsartproject #kidsartclass #artvideos 
#letsmakeartkids #letsmakeart #letsmakeartmatter

As I’m getting prepared to launch and share what Keenan and I are working on, thoughts swim through my head: 

“No one cares”
“You’re not ready”
“Who do you think you are?”
“Your program ended for a reason so why try something else?”
“Why don’t you get a real job?”

I know harsh right! We wouldn’t say these things to our people so why would do we say them to ourselves? 

I don’t have all the answers and yes I have a mix of fear and excitement and butterflies running through my head and heart and stomach as I type this. But at the end of the day I fully believe that we are meant to share our gifts to the world. So if you’re like me, feeling a little scared to share something whether it be a big launch or a painting, or a conversation you need to have, please don’t let your inner critic get in the way. The world needs what is in your heart ❤️ 

PS: If you want to join our new email list, we’ll be announcing our new adventure so soon! 
See I’m trying :)

#realtalk #comingsoon #communityovercompetition #artistreels #artistsoninstagram #artistlife

Today marks the start of a new daily practice. My goal is to create with a word in mind and see what happens!

Content. You might read content like social media content to share. But I’m actually thinking of content as an adjective not a noun - a state of peaceful happiness. 

And right now that word speaks to me. I got to visit with my best friend @kimknievel this past weekend with our two little boys. Our life looks so different than when we first met 10+ years ago and what she said to me was “You seem content and in a good way. You are happy, you feel light, and it’s amazing to see you as a mama.” 

I paused and looked at her with a huge smile and said “gosh you are so right :)” 

So much has happened this year and it came with a whole new set of routine or lack there of (you mamas understand!), a new normal with our family life, and starting a new business! So to sit here, not feeling bitter or sad or confused, and instead feeling peace and joy as I look over at my little Koda figuring out how to crawl, it feels so so sweet.

Thank you to those who have supported me this year from my mama friends, to my family, to our @theabunchcrew Founding Members, and to Keenan. I am settling into this new identity and I feel so content ❤️ It’s been awhile since I’ve been this excited to create art again so we’ll see what happens! 

#artistsoninstagram #watercolor #lettering #painting #quotes #motherhood

I admit, this one got a little moody! That’s okay right?! I wanted to portray depth and this is what came out of me :)

PS: Swipe to see a video of me figuring out the cloud layout. I’ve been having way too much fun with tearing paper!

When I hear the word balance I giggle. 
“Work life balance” 
“Eat a balanced diet” 
“Balancing the kids schedule”
Who can do it all?!?! If you have the answers please do tell me 🙋🏻‍♀️😂🙏🏻

But you know what feels balanced to me. Nature. Specifically the sun and sky against the water. Whether the sun radiated brightly or the waves were crashing, together the sun and ocean felt balanced. 

I sure do miss my California beach walks and @swellpress, but I hope to channel those moments to keep me balanced even miles away 💙🌊🌅

PS: If something in nature helps you feel balanced too, I’d love to know!

Some of you saw on my IG stories that I didn’t get to finish this one yesterday. It was a good reminder to be kind to myself. 

Because instead of beating myself up that I set this personal challenge that I didn’t complete, I saw and recognized that my body had different plans and that was okay. 

I needed to choose self care like @2dayilook4unicorns reminded me ❤️ and know that I could come back tomorrow and finish it. 

And this afternoon I did just that. I showed up and cutout a simple sun, added birds flying in pencil and stepped away. I smudged the birds by accident but decided to leave it as a reminder that life gets blurry sometimes, but it’s all part of the beautiful process unfolding and to not erase it.

Yesterday marked 34 years around the sun ☀️ and a new adventure with us sitting around our family table cheering on Koda to try his first solid food, avocado!

As I looked around at this simple but pure moment, I was filled with so much love. “This is my life, these are my people, and we are making this place a home.”

I am still learning what it means to be a mama/bonus mom while loving on our new art business @theabunchcrew, but my hope for this next year is to continue showing up how I can. 

Sometimes that will mean a frozen pizza dinner and other times that will mean learning how to cook a family meal. 

So if you have a favorite {easy} and yummy meal you love to cook for your family, can you help a sister out and share :) Pinterest is great but real life people like you all are way better! 

Thank you for the birthday wishes and cheers to the simple moments seeing the growth in ourselves and these little humans while giggling along the way! 

With lots of love, Nicole

Some of you might remember me sharing art made by the talented @iuliastration when I was going through a lot of changes in my career. Her art and words spoke to me in the moment as she wrote “Your heart knows the way. Run in that direction.” 

Using that as my inspiration, I sat down and completed this art that has been on my desk for a few days. To me it represents the hills and valleys that life presents. It can be easy to feel lost and overwhelmed with what direction to go. And it’s even easier to not do anything because then you won’t let anyone or yourself down. 

But what if there is a way to walk a path that feels like less resistance. Less like trying to impress others. Less fighting for them to see your worth. Less striving to climb a ladder only to be knocked down. 

Instead run towards what feels good and true. Run towards that crazy idea even if others are nay sayers. Do it. Run to the light. If it lights you up, it’s for a reason ☀️ trust that.

Share with a friend to encourage them to do the thing ☀️💛

We did something wild and totally new – we bought a camper!! 
It’s been a dream of Keenan’s (he says “for at least two weeks!” ☺️) and when his sister was selling hers we said “let’s do it!” 

But here’s the best part, if for any wild reason you’re thinking of making your way out to Missouri in the future you have a place to stay! We are renting this camper out through @outdoorsy 🌲🍃☀️I’ll add the link in stories :) 

We definitely have nerves right now (good nerves) as this is a whole new business venture for us. Actually the same nerves when we started the @theabunchcrew, but hey if you don’t do things scared, you’re not doing it right, right? Isn’t that how the saying goes?! Gosh we hope so! 

Have you or your family gone on family road trips or stayed in a camper? Tell us!

My vision for this one started out moody with dark trees, no sun and a gloomy sky. 
(Swipe through to see what i thought was a finished painting).
I didn’t quite like it but I really wanted to be done and post it. 

However, my instincts were ALSO telling me “nope, not done yet.” I decided to let it sit for a few days.

Circle back to today, and after church while Koda and Keenan napped, I came back with fresh eyes. I decided to add flowers and more color like you see. It was light and happy and I immediately felt a wave of peace. 

It hit me. 

Maybe this was God’s way of telling me that he wasn’t done with ME yet. That there were some hard and unexpected valleys I had to go through earlier this year, gloomy and without sun. But there was, and is, flowers and sun and peace for me. 

We all have hills and valleys each unique to us. And gosh sometimes the lows are hard and confusing and messy. But maybe art can be part of the healing. When we take a step back from a painting (or a hard situation) with fresh eyes, maybe just maybe, a pink sun, more color, and a new perspective are what is needed to heal ☀️

And a cute little Koda with 2 teeth are the best bonus :)

You know what’s interesting, lettering used to be my jam. It’s what I was known for and what I loved. I taught my lettering workshops in-person, online and through my books. I think that’s when a lot of you discovered me!

Over the past several years you probably noticed I’ve been through a lot of life changes, career changes and art changes.

But as the rhythm of life continues, I feel lettering coming back into my life and my heart. And gosh it feels SO good!

So what does that mean for you? It means I’ll be sharing more lettering and tips that I can pass on. Get ready! 

The @theabunchcrew has already gotten a piece of what I’m excited to continue to share ☀️ And if you have a word that means something to you in this season of life, please let me know. I want to letter words that speak to us ❤️

Just in case you need this reminder — the world needs you ❤️

Share with a friend you want to love on and remind them of this too!

Just as we evolve, our styles can too.

This word was suggested by @jilliebeans704 and it spoke right to my heart. 

Often times, we take note of the big changes. The milestones we hit or don’t hit. The big move or change in jobs. The people who hurt us or the replaying of conversations we had. 

But what if the smallest change in our heart is where we can evolve the most. What if we allow light to shine through a crack in that wall we put up to protect ourselves. 

It may seem too much for you today (me too) but when I letter and change one tiny thing like the space between the letters or the size of the letter itself, it reminds me that we can create anew. 

You got this. We got this. Let’s evolve.

Use these steps to do this style with any word! 

1. Use a pencil to draw your bubble numbers. 
TIP: Use a white crayon and outline. This will help to resist the watercolor.

2. Paint watercolor blobs around the numbers and then paint black in the open areas.

3. Let it dry. Then use paint markers or gel pens to outline the numbers and draw fireworks. I love to use @posca_usa and @uniballco metallic gel pens 🎇🎆

4. Add a shadow to the numbers. I used black watercolor and painted a thin line along the outside left edge of the numbers.

That’s it! Like I said, save this and use these steps and techniques for other words and occasions in the future! Maybe LOVE for Valentine’s Day coming up ❤️
